results.description:
The Live Laugh Love Anniversary Wine Box by WineforaWedding® is a unique and personalized gift that couples will enjoy on future wedding anniversary celebrations. Perfect Wedding, Anniversary, or Engagement Gift! Proudly handmade in the USA.

Our patented box has three separate compartments for wine. As the couple reaches each anniversary, they reveal and enjoy a bottle of aged wine. These unique wine boxes are a truly creative way to toast newlyweds for years to come! 

(wine NOT included)


HOW TO ORDER:
1 » Choose the Anniversary "Open On" years from the drop-down menu. 

2 » Include your phone number (for shipping purposes only) 


WHAT'S INCLUDED:
» 3 embossed foil seals. 
(seals each lid once you have added wine)

» Recyclable, crinkle-cut, kraft paper inside each compartment. 
(protects and insulates your wine)


ADDING WINE:
Once you receive the wine box, go to your local wine shop and purchase 3 bottles of wine that will age appropriately to the "Open On" anniversary dates you selected. Place the bottles inside each compartment and seal each lid with a foil seal.

» Each inside compartment dimensions are 13" T x 3-3/4" W. We based our compartment measurements to hold a bottle of Dom Perignon - anything larger than that will not fit.


ABOUT OUR PRODUCT:  
» All boxes are made to order.

Every wine box is made in the USA and crafted from wood harvested in a responsible way. Our time-released, message in the box design is patent protected and unique. All of our wine boxes are engraved, especially for our customers, at our workshop in High Ridge, Missouri.


HOW WE GIVE BACK:  
To reduce our impact on the environment one tree is planted for every box we sell.


OVERALL BOX DIMENSIONS:  13-5/8"H x 14-1/8"W x 4-1/2"D

results.title: YES Book Folding Pattern -- 165 Folds (330 numbered pages). PDF digital download. Includes free How-To Guide with 3 free patterns.
results.description:
**Free How-To Video** Watch my free book folding class on YouTube. Master the art of book folding using my simple method. It's easy and fun. Go to www.youtube.com. Search for "have fun book folding" in the search bar at the top of the page. Click on the video "Book Folding Art Class -- Master the Basics of Book Folding." Join me and start book folding today!

Say yes to pursuing your dreams. Say yes to loving more, to forgiving more.  Say yes to embracing the beauty of life.  With this pattern you can create an important reminder to say yes instead of no.

What you get:
1. PDF file of the "yes" pattern to download and print.
2. Free PDF file of my how-to guide, "Traditional Book Folding: a Step-by-Step Illustrated Guide." This 68-page, fully illustrated e-book includes 3 free, printable patterns for you to fold: Rabbit, Petite Heart, and Ice Skate.

"yes" pattern information:
Method: measure, mark, and fold in centimeters/millimeters
Number of Folds: 165 (requires a book with at least 330 numbered pages)
Height of "yes" image: 9 cm (3.5 in)
Required height of book: at least 22 cm (8.75 in)
Difficulty level: Intermediate

My graphic designer and I developed the font in "yes" especially for book folding. The elegant, classic-style letters are large enough to read easily, but they have page counts low enough to make them quicker to fold.

If you're new to the art of book folding, begin by downloading and reading "Traditional Book Folding: a Step-by-Step Illustrated Guide." You'll receive a free PDF file of this 68-page e-book (electronic book) with your purchase of the "yes" pattern. I wrote the e-book especially for beginners. It contains my simple, straightforward methods that will take you from novice to book folding expert. It includes 3 free, printable patterns to get you started on the road to book folding success: Rabbit, Petite Heart, and Ice Skate.

Upon payment, Etsy will email a link to you.  Click on the link to download both the "yes" pattern and the e-book, so you can begin folding right away. The pattern includes a photo of the completed book. You may print the pattern as many times as you want to fold it. You may also print the e-book. Compatible with both PC and Mac, the PDF files display well on tablets, laptops, and desktop computers. They may not display well on the small screen of a smartphone.

I personally design and test-fold all of my patterns. The photos in this listing show the actual book that I folded using the "yes" pattern. I used the methods that I teach in "Traditional Book Folding: a Step-by-Step Illustrated Guide."

Although you may not sell or distribute my e-book and patterns, you may sell any book(s) you fold using my e-book and patterns.
